        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Lets say I have an app running a subdirectory \"ABC\". I have set the base url in the application.ini file as I am using the built in application\/bootstrapping mechanism. Attempts to access a url such as \"http:\/\/localhost\/ABC\/controller\/action\" fail because the \"setPathInfo\" method on the HTTP Request object is setting the \"pathInfo\" to \"C\/controller\/action\". The \"C\" is then interpreted as the module.\n\nI traced the problem down to ~ line 605 of \"Zend\/Controller\/Request\/Http.php\". \n\n{code:title=Http.php}\nif ((null !== $baseUrl)\n                && (false === ($pathInfo = substr($requestUri, strlen($baseUrl)))))\n{code}\n\n...apparently should be...\n\n{code:title=Http.php}\nif ((null !== $baseUrl)\n                && (false === ($pathInfo = substr($requestUri, strlen($baseUrl)+1))))\n{code}\n\nI'm running PHP 5.2.6 on Ubuntu in case there is some difference in how substr operates across versions."
        },
